ewport` call that is still receiving logical pixels (glViewport always requires physical pixels as explained in `HDPIUtils` javadoc). \r\n\r\nIt is  noticeable as shown in #6454 on a simple project with no `Viewport`. When using a `Viewport` this problem did not reproduce because it makes its own `glViewport` calls on `apply()` implementation.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/libgdx/libgdx/issues/6455/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/libgdx/libgdx/issues/6455/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null}},"event":"cross-referenced"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/libgdx/libgdx/issues/comments/799475171","html_url":"https://github.com/libgdx/libgdx/issues/6454#issuecomment-799475171","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/libgdx/libgdx/issues/6454","id":799475171,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDc5OTQ3NTE3MQ==","user":{"login":"obigu","id":1794492,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE3OTQ0OTI=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1794492?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu","html_url":"https://github.com/obigu","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2021-03-15T14:42:27Z","updated_at":"2021-03-15T14:53:12Z","body":"**The information on my previous comment was not correct, I've decided to delete it not to cause any confusion.**\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/libgdx/libgdx/pull/6455 fixes this issue.\r\n\r\nIndependently of the fix (and once it's merged), because of the change to support HDPI modes and make logical pixels default, the basic Gdx Setup template doesn't look the same on an Android device than on an iOS device both sharing the same resolution. On iOS or Lwjgl3 (backends that support HDPI modes), the badlogic image will look similar in size independently of the device screen resolution, on the other hand, on Android it will be smaller the higher the resolution on the device.\r\n\r\nThe same applies to libGDX tests, most of which don't use `Viewport` and scale differently depending on the backend. Most libGDX tests look tiny on Android high DPI screens and that is something worth having a look.\r\n\r\nWe can have a separate discussion on this topic if we want. The important thing is that the bug is fixed and behaviour is now the expected.\r\n","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/libgdx/libgdx/issues/comments/799475171/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":1,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"obigu","id":1794492,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE3OTQ0OTI=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1794492?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu","html_url":"https://github.com/obigu","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/repo